value.value: Pericardial effusion in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Pericarditis Associated with Post-Acute Sequelae of SARS-CoV-2 Infection

value.value: Pericarditis that started during probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 and persisted beyond four weeks after the initial diagnosis of COVID-19.

label.value: Acute Ischemic Limb Related to COVID-19

value.value: A sudden or severe decrease in limb perfusion in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19, usually producing new or worsening symptoms or signs, and often threatening limb viability or resulting in limb amputation.
A finding noted on examination of the functioning of the nervous system.
The process of clarifying the aims of care, communicating wishes and goals for medical care in the event of an emergency, and documenting those wishes or plan in an advance directive.
Organic or inorganic compounds that contain nitrogen as an integral part of the molecule.
A grouping of occupations and fields of study.
Polyneuropathy and myopathy arising in intensive care unit patients.

Polyneuropathy arising in intensive care unit patients.  It is a common complication of severe sepsis and is thought to represent a neurologic manifestation of systemic inflammatory response syndrome (SIRS).

label.value: Postural Orthostatic Tachycardia Syndrome Associated with Post-Acute Sequelae of SARS-CoV-2 Infection

value.value: Postural orthostatic tachycardia syndrome (POTS) that started during probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 and persisted at least three months after the initial diagnosis of COVID-19.
A pregnancy complication in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
The pressure applied by the ventilator at the end of each breath to ensure that the alveoli are not so prone to collapse.
Presyncope in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Prior COVID-19 Infection With Residual Sequelae of Post-Acute COVID-19

value.value: A finding indicating that there is prior evidence of COVID-19 in an individual who has residual sequelae of post-acute COVID-19.

label.value: Prior COVID-19 Infection Without Residual Sequelae of Post-Acute COVID-19

value.value: A finding indicating that there is prior evidence of COVID-19 in an individual who has no residual sequelae of post-acute COVID-19.

A presumed acute COVID-19 infection as evidenced by detection of SARS-CoV-2 by antigen test in a respiratory specimen, by meeting clinical criteria and epidemiological linkage criteria for COVID-19 with no confirmatory laboratory testing performed, or by a death certificate that lists COVID-19 disease or SARS-CoV-2 as an underlying cause of death or a significant condition contributing to death with no confirmatory laboratory evidence of SARS-CoV-2.
Rapid or severe onset or rapid progression of pulmonary edema causing significant hypoxemia or the need for supplemental oxygen.

label.value: Pulmonary Thromboembolic Disease Associated with Post-Acute Sequelae of SARS-CoV-2 Infection

value.value: Intravascular migration of a venous embolus to the pulmonary arterial circulation, microvascular thrombosis in the pulmonary capillaries, or pulmonary artery thrombus in situ diagnosed by a positive pulmonary angiogram, an unequivocally positive helical CT scan, a high-probability ventilation-perfusion scan, or autopsy that started during probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 and persisted beyond four weeks after the initial diagnosis of COVID-19.
Pulmonary embolism in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
The ratio of fraction of inspired oxygen (FiO2) to positive end-expiratory pressure (PEEP). This measured value may be adjusted on a mechanical ventilator to optimize treatment.

A predictive measure of right ventricular failure after inferior myocardial infarction and left ventricular assist device implantation.  It is calculated from the ratio of the pulmonary artery pulse pressure to right atrial pressure (calculated systolic pulmonary arterial pressure - diastolic pulmonary pressure)/right atrial pressure).
A low-pitch harsh, grating sound heard on auscultation of the lungs during inspiration and expiration that is caused by inflamed pleura layers rubbing together.
Rhabdomyolysis in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
An indication that SARS-CoV-2 continued to be detected in a patient's biological samples beyond the presumptive infectious period of acute COVID-19.
Seizure in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Thrusts I II III IV VI

value.value: Systemic vasodilation leading to decreased blood flow to organs in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
A type of vascular stent that is biodegradable.

A metallic vascular stent encased by a synthetic membrane, often polytetrafluoroethylene or polyurethane, developed to prevent restenosis from proliferation of tissue as may be the case with uncovered stents.

label.value: Cardiac Structural Abnormalities Associated with Post-Acute Sequelae of SARS-CoV-2 Infection

value.value: Cardiac structural changes or abnormalities characterized by myocardial systolic dysfunction or myocardial edema or fibrosis on non-invasive cardiac imaging that started during probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 and persisted beyond four weeks after the initial diagnosis of COVID-19.

label.value: Sudden Cardiac Death Related to COVID-19

value.value: Sudden cardiac death in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Sudden Cardiac Death with Return of Spontaneous Circulation Related to COVID-19

value.value: Unexpected death caused by sudden cardiac arrest with asystole, pulseless electrical activity, sustained ventricular tachycardia, or ventricular fibrillation in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 despite successful return of spontaneous circulation (ROSC).
Non-curative therapy given to treat symptomatic SARS-CoV-2 infection.
Syncope in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

Consists of three persons appointed by the President, who by virtue of their training, experience, and background are exceptionally qualified to appraise the National Cancer Program. Two of the members of the Panel are distinguished scientists or physicians. Members are appointed for three-year terms. Established by Congress, December 23, 1971.

label.value: Supraventricular Tachyarrhythmia Other than Atrial Fibrillation or Atrial Flutter Associated with Post-Acute Sequelae of SARS-CoV-2 Infection

value.value: Supraventricular tachycardia other than atrial fibrillation or atrial flutter in a patient without prior history of atrial tachyarrhythmias that started during probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 and persisted beyond four weeks after the initial diagnosis of COVID-19.

label.value: Sustained Atrial Tachyarrhythmia Related to COVID-19 other than Atrial Fibrillation or Atrial Flutter

value.value: A supraventricular tachycardia, including AV nodal re-entry, orthodromic re-entrant tachycardia, multifocal atrial tachycardia, other atrial tachycardia that lasts more then 30 seconds in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
An interventional procedure to remove a blood clot from a peripheral artery, excluding acute ischemic stroke.
An interventional procedure to remove a blood clot from a pulmonary artery in a patient with acute pulmonary embolism.
An interventional procedure to remove a blood clot from an artery in a patient with acute ischemic stroke.
Medical treatment to break up a blood clot from a pulmonary artery in a patient with acute pulmonary embolism.
Medical treatment to break up a blood clot from an artery in a patient with acute ischemic stroke.
Thrombophilia in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
The time that mechanical circulatory support was utilized.
Experimental pathology; the study of disease processes by the manipulation of the natural state of an organism.

label.value: Time of Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation for Cardiac Arrest

value.value: The time that cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) for cardiac arrest was performed.
The time that percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI) was performed.
Blood clot formation in the small blood vessels of the body in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Sustained Ventricular Arrhythmia Related to COVID-19

value.value: Ventricular tachycardia or ventricular fibrillation lasting greater than or equal to 30 seconds, or requiring direct current cardioversion (DCCV) in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
